# NovaSpend Architecture

## Layer boundaries

- **presentation/** — Flutter UI, Provider (ChangeNotifier ViewModels). May import domain + l10n.
- **domain/** — entities, abstract repositories, use cases. Pure Dart only. No Flutter, Provider, or l10n.
- **data/** — datasources, models (DTOs), `repository_impl.dart`. Implements domain repositories.

Dependency flow: `presentation → domain ← data`.

## Feature folder layout

```
features/<feature>/
├── data/
│   ├── datasource/
│   ├── models/
│   └── repository_impl.dart
├── domain/
│   ├── entities/
│   ├── repositories/<feature>_repository.dart
│   └── usecases/
└── presentation/
    ├── pages/
    ├── widgets/
    └── provider/
```

Features: `auth`, `transactions`, `categories`, `budgets`, `analytics`, `settings`.

## Data flow

```
UI (pages/widgets)
  → Provider (presentation/provider/)
  → UseCase (domain/usecases/)
  → Repository abstract (domain/repositories/)
  → RepositoryImpl (data/repository_impl.dart)
  → DataSource (Firestore / webhook / local)
```

## Provider conventions

- One ChangeNotifier per screen or cohesive flow in `presentation/provider/`.
- Providers call use cases, never datasources directly.
- Map domain `Failure` to user-facing strings in presentation via `context.l10n`.

## Entity / model mapping

- **entities/** — domain objects used by use cases and presentation.
- **models/** — Firestore/JSON DTOs with `toEntity()` / `fromEntity()` or similar mappers.
- Align entities with backend schema in `shared/types/schema.ts`.

## Backend integration

- Auth: Firebase Auth; use `uid` as tenant key.
- Read: Firestore `users/{uid}/transactions` (realtime snapshots).
- Ingest: POST to `ingestTransactionForUser` with `X-User-Id` header (not client Firestore writes until Phase 5 rules).
- Settings map to `User` + `UserSettings` in Firestore.

## File naming

- Abstract repo: `<feature>_repository.dart`
- Implementation: `repository_impl.dart`
- Use cases: `<verb>_<noun>.dart` (e.g. `get_transactions.dart`)
- Providers: `<feature>_provider.dart` or `<screen>_provider.dart`

## DI

Register repos, use cases, and providers in `lib/core/di/injection.dart` via GetIt (`sl`).
